# Settings Architecture — Two Axes

## Never confuse ENVIRONMENT and ENV

```
ENVIRONMENT = dev | staging | production | test   → deployment context
ENV         = None | "admin" | "graphql"          → Django process role
```

## ENV constants — always use, never hardcode strings

```python
# config/settings/env_settings.py
ENV_ADMIN = "admin"
ENV_GRAPHQL = "graphql"
ENV = None  # default = dev (admin + graphql in one process)
```

## Specialized settings files — one line each

```python
# config/settings_admin.py
from .settings.base import *
ENV = ENV_ADMIN

# config/settings_graphql.py
from .settings.base import *
ENV = ENV_GRAPHQL
```

## urls.py — always conditional on settings.ENV

```python
# ✅ Correct
if ENV is None or ENV == ENV_ADMIN:
    urlpatterns += [path('', admin.site.urls)]
    urlpatterns += [path('graphql/', GraphQLView.as_view(graphiql=True))]
elif ENV == ENV_GRAPHQL:
    urlpatterns += [path('graphql/', GraphQLView.as_view(
        graphiql=False,
        validation_rules=[DisableIntrospectionRule(), MaxQueryDepthRule(7)],
    ))]

# ❌ Never hardcode behavior
urlpatterns = [path('admin/', admin.site.urls)]  # wrong path AND wrong logic
```

## Security — always driven by ENVIRONMENT

```python
# ✅ Correct — in security_settings.py
_IS_SECURE = ENVIRONMENT in ('production', 'staging')
SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT = _IS_SECURE

# ❌ Never hardcode
SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT = True
```

## ENVIRONMENT must be validated at startup

```python
if ENVIRONMENT not in ('dev', 'staging', 'production', 'test'):
    raise ImproperlyConfigured(f"Invalid ENVIRONMENT: {ENVIRONMENT!r}")
```

## Production Docker — one container per role

```yaml
app-admin:    DJANGO_SETTINGS_MODULE: config.settings_admin    # ENV="admin"
app-graphql:  DJANGO_SETTINGS_MODULE: config.settings_graphql  # ENV="graphql"
app-idle:     command: sleep infinity                           # for shell/migrate
workers:      DJANGO_SETTINGS_MODULE: config.settings_graphql  # management commands
```

## CSP middleware — only on HTML-serving processes

```python
# In base.py — CSP is useless on pure GraphQL (JSON only)
if ENV != ENV_GRAPHQL:
    MIDDLEWARE.insert(1, "csp.middleware.CSPMiddleware")
```
